    • Method Detail

      • getContentType

        java.lang.String getContentType()
        Get the content type value for this type definition. Legal content type values are 'empty', 'simple', 'element only', or 'mixed'.
        Returns:
        the content type value

      • getBlockValue

        java.lang.String getBlockValue()
        Get the value of the 'block' attribute. Legal values are '#all' or a whitespace-separated list containing the values 'extension' or 'restriction'.
        Returns:
        the value, or the schema 'blockDefault' value if the attribute is not present

      • isAbstract

        boolean isAbstract()
        Get the value of the 'abstract' attribute as a boolean. Abstract types must be substituted with valid derived types at runtime, or the XML instance will not be valid. Type overloading in an XML instance is accomplished using the xsi:type attribute.
        Returns:
        the value, or false if the attribute is not present

      • getModelGroupDefinition

        XSDModelGroupDefinition getModelGroupDefinition()
        Get the model group definition component that defines the element content of this complex type. Model groups are one way to define complex type content, and are not required.
        Returns:
        the model group definition component, or null if not set

      • getModelGroupReference

        XSDModelGroupReference getModelGroupReference()
        Get the model group reference component that is used to extend or restrict model group content.
        Returns:
        the model group reference component, or null if not set

      • getAttributeComponents

        XSDComponentList getAttributeComponents()
        Get the list of attribute components for this complex type. List elements can be of type XSDAttributeDeclaration, XSDAttributeReference, XSDAttributeGroupReference, or XSDAttributeWildcard.
        Returns:
        the list of attribute components

      • getSubstituteTypeDefinitions

        XSDComponentList getSubstituteTypeDefinitions()
        Get the list of complex type definition components that are valid substitutes for this complex type. List elements are of type XSDComplexTypeDefinition.
        Returns:
        the list of substitutable complex types

      • getSOAPArrayTypeReferenceValue

        javax.xml.namespace.QName getSOAPArrayTypeReferenceValue()
        Get the SOAP 'arrayType' attribute value as a qualified name. SOAP array types are declared using complex content restrictions according to the rules of the W3C SOAP 1.1 specification, Section 5.
        Returns:
        the SOAP array bounds value

      • getSOAPArrayBounds

        int getSOAPArrayBounds()
        Get the SOAP array bounds from the 'arrayType' attribute value. Array bounds are declared by appending '[]' to the qualified type name for a one-dimensional array, or '[,]' or '[][]' for a two-dimensional array.
        Returns:
        1 or 2, or 0 if this is not a SOAP array

      • getSOAPArrayTypeDefinition

        XSDTypeDefinition getSOAPArrayTypeDefinition()
        Get the type definition component that is used for the elements of a SOAP array type definition.
        Returns:
        the SOAP array type definition component, or null if unresolved
